roughout the world from the highlytrained flight crew to the engineers and maintenance teams that support them at each stop our people make the difference we rely on a global logistics and engineering team that efficiently plans and tailors whatever resources are needed to support aroundtheclock operations we know the best people become even more effective when they are continually provided with innovative technology from a global supply chain management system to global aircraﬅ monitoring to a shared digital records library we make sure that our teams can get what they need quickly to keep things running smoothly for our customers all of this is supported at our corporate headquarters and global operations center in dallas texas where we help accelerate the integration of advanced tools systems and processes for specific flightoperations support maintenance and technicalsupport functions every day around the clock we are looking for people who can not only utilize these systems but help us continue to evolve and push the boundaries of innovation in our industry if you’re a go getter and problemsolver and are interested in joining a team dedicated to quickly mobilizing customer solutions for a global customer base then chc wants to talk to you we offer challenging opportunities to learn and grow so you can reach beyond to achieve your career goals check out our current openings and apply today   careers contact us press releases ethics privacy policy offshore transport services  chc helicopter menu flight schedule what we do offshore transport flight schedule search  rescue sar emergency medical services ems helione mro services flight training offshore expertise that runs wide  deep decades of overwater flying in extremely demanding conditions have honed unmatched knowledge skill—and leadership—in offshore transportation for companies that discover and produce oil and natural gas each year our people carry more than one million passengers to and from the ships and platforms that make up their offshore workplaces today deepwater and ultradeepwater reserves represent the vast majority of the worlds new oil and gas discoveries overwhelmingly in places where we have wellestablished capabilities off the coasts of australia brazil norway the united kingdom and several nations in africa as our customers continue to go further to explore and produce oil and gas chcs worldclass advanced fleet innovative technology and global reach make us uniquely able to understand and safely meet their needs irweblink thank you for your interest in ir solutions you have reached this page because the url you have requested is no longer available or you do not have permission to view it for more information on the most comprehensive ir web site management tool available please click here if you have any questions email irsupportsnlcom or call   and ask for an ir solutions sales representative please click here to return to the main snl financial homepage   chc helicopter sa credit rating  moodys yes no about moodyscareersregulatory affairsterms of usecontact usabout moodyscompany overviewinvestor relationsmedia relationscorporate social responsibilityalumni go there are too many sessions currently in use on this account log in cancel research  ratings overviewratings newsrating methodologiesratings disclosuresratings performanceregulatory affairscode of professional conductsector in depthlook up a ratingfind an analystinteractive chartsmarket segmentcorporatesfinancial institutionsstructured financemanaged investmentsinfrastructure  project financesovereign  supranationalsubsovereignus public financeregionnorth americalatin america  caribbeaneurope middle east  africaasia pacificresearch typeissuer researchindustry  sector researchmethodologycapital markets researchdefault  ratings analyticseconomic researchdata reportspolitical  economic groupemerging marketseuropean unionasiapacific economic cooperation apecassociation of southeast asian nations ase