sition from his post as president of european operations and take over leadership of chcs search and rescue divisiontilmann gabriel has done an outstanding job with european operations and his enthusiasm for growing the sar segment of our business makes him the obvious candidate to assume responsibility for tackling the difficult task of growing this business explained mr amelioin addition to mr gabriels transition scott pinfield has been appointed interim leader of the new flying operations division mr pinfield has a sterling reputation with chc helicopter having contributed to the european operations team as chief operating officer and latterly as managing director european operations mr pinfield will be responsible for integrating chcs european operations and global operations divisions into a single flying operations division benefits of this integration include the ability to deliver common standards on a global basis an improved consistency of product enhanced safety levels and increased levels of customer servicechc also announced that michael oneill will assume the position of chief legal counsel eventually replacing martin lockyer who has announced his retirement from chc mr oneill joins chc after serving as senior vice president and general counsel for the lenovo group where he was responsible for all legal affairs contracts government affairs and security for the companyid like to thank martin for his dedication and passion for chc and i am grateful that he has agreed to stay on to assist with michaels transition into the role said mr amelio during his tenure with chc mr lockyer has been involved in every ma transaction refinancing and high profile operational issue chc has completed examples include the acquisition of chc by first reserve in  restructuring of chcs nigerian operations recent successful bond offering and providing legal oversight to the many commercial contracts to which chc is a partychc helicopter is the worlds largest helicopter services company specializing in the transport of personnel to offshore oil platforms the chc helicopter group of companies is also a worldleader in the provision of civilian searchandrescue operations with major contracts in the uk ireland and australia and a world leader in helicopter maintenance through its delta british columbiabased division helione  for full biographies of chc helicopters senior leadership team please visit wwwchccareblogsharetweetsharepopular in the communitytrump to sessions ‘you’re kind of fired maybe’ reactionsdiscover it  out of  avg by k customersdiscover cardsponsoredprotesting trumps military transgender ban reactionsmcdonalds worker puts everyone off ice cream with disgusting photos   reactionsprincess diana’s brother says he was lied to about princes william harry following dianas coffin reactionswomen everywhere should carry this tiny devicesiren songsponsoredsmuggled animals reactionsamazon is hiring reactionsluis fonsi on justin biebers spanish despacito hitting no  reactionstrunk club making sense of styletrunk clubsponsoredscaramucci deflects questions on white house leaks to priebus reactionsangelina jolie reveals bell’s palsy diagnosis — as she says children are still ‘healing’ from brad pitt divorce reactionspakistani council orders revenge rape of yearold girl reactionsthe travel card that is breaking thwise breadsponsoredcolorado woman defies immigration and customs enforcement from church sanctuary reactionsthe note trumps ban on transgender troops blindsides dc reactionsus parents are pulling their children out of boy scouts over donald trumps drunk stepdad speechkashco you just cant take him anywherejoin the conversation  k chc helicopters chc helicopters continues to roll out aims to its bases around the world having initially implemented aims since  as their fully integrated crew management and operations control solution in selected countries chc helicopters have quickly identified the benefits derived from using aims and as a result have opted to extend implementation throughout many more of their bases worldwide   chc’s decision to expand the use of aims across operations in different locations underlines aims unparalleled ability to support manage and develop a business model that effectively caters for the needs of each individual country   george g bethanis head of corporate communications   “it is extremely rewarding to see that our product is helping the world’s largest commercial helicopter operator evolve and we will continue to be by their chc helicopter’s side to help consolidate and build on this success” more news aims user conference   new spanish airlines choose aims north  south american airlines switched to aims falcon aviation  saudi gulf airlines choose to aims the upcoming aims user conference in spring  will be hosted in athens greece scheduled regularly every  months in a city voted by the airline members of the aims community aims user conferences offer existing airline three new spanish airline have signed with aims this year binter canarias swiftair and canary fly all have chosen aims crew management and operations control systems to automate their operations during the last few years the aims system has risen to become three more airline from the north and south american continent have switched to aims in  national airlines usa air creebec canada and avior venezuela all have chose the aims crew management and operations control airline software solutions to automate their operations our market share in uae and saudi arabia is expanding with the addition of two new airlines to our clientele in the region falcon aviation services services has chosen aims crew management operations control and business aviation flight quotation systems to automate its read more read more read more read more air asia expanding our already successful market share through the asia pacific region aims is extremely delighted to announce that the air asia group an award winning lowcost